post_text:
Onsite registration for the 2020-2021 school year has been moved to online registration due to Covid-19. All new students, and returning students must register online. If you are new, please create a new parent portal account. If you are a returner, please use the parent portal account you already have. DO NOT register them as a new student. For more infomation, please visit our website under parents for more information.

If you have any questions or would feel more comfortable doing your student's registration in person, please contact Jessica Stone at jessica.stone@bosquevilleisd.org to set up a time to come in person to register. I will be more than happy to walk you through the process. I can also help you set everything up via email!

post_text: This is an updated message for Bosqueville ISD parents regarding the 20-21 school year. As most of you know on Tuesday, July 21st the McLennan County Health Department closed schools in our County to in-person instruction until Tuesday, September 8, 2020. BISD will begin Remote (Asynchronous) Instruction on our regularly scheduled start date of Thursday, August 13, 2020, for all students. You will be receiving an email or you can check the school website for detailed information.

Texas Education Agency
June 1 at 3:17 PM ·

The P-EBT food benefit is for families & students who:

🔹️Qualify for free/reduced-price meals in the 2019-20 school year;
🔹️Attend a Community Eligibility Provision or Provision 2 campus that offers free meals to all students; or
🔹️Received SNAP food benefits in March 2020.

To learn more, visit: bit.ly/2XdQfTB

shared_text:
Bosqueville ISD
May 26 at 1:49 PM ·

Guidelines and Criteria for Attending Bosqueville ISD Graduation Ceremony:

1. Each graduate is allowed to have ten (10) attendees.

2. Attendees must be with the Graduate at their assigned time in order to be allowed into the Stadium.

3. Each attendee must present a COVID-19 screening form at the Graduation ceremony. These forms will be issued to each Graduate for distribution prior to the ceremony.

4. Any person arriving on their own without a screening form and not with a Graduate will be turned away and not be allowed to enter the stadium.

post_text:
Free facebook live stream from Region 12: May 13th @7pm
Even when life is interrupted by a global pandemic, life is still happening. We still have homes to run, we still have to find things we need. We're trying to keep our families together, yet safely apart and we're trying to keep our kids learning when their school buildings stand silent. In this brief conversation, we'll explore what keeps us together as parents and educators and discuss what we have to guard against from ripping us apart. We're not necessarily experiencing it like everyone else. But one thing is for certain; we're all experiencing it. We're living through the same storm, but experiencing it in a different boat.

post_text: As you may have heard, Governor Abbott issued an executive order today closing schools for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. We are sad and heartbroken that we won't see our students each day and continue to make memories with them over the next few weeks. The BISD leadership team will be meeting early next week to make plans on closing out this year. We will work to the best of our abilities to ensure the Class of 2020 is recognized for all of their work and celebrate their accomplishments. We encourage everyone to continue monitoring their email, Google Classroom, Remind, district/campus web pages, and campus Facebook pages for updates.

post_text:
As most of you know Governor Abbott issued an Executive Order today. Included in that order was the closing of all schools in Texas through April 3rd.

Bosqueville ISD will continue the “work at home” delivery method of instruction for all students that was started on Wednesday, March 18th. We will continue to communicate with parents, staff and students through e-mail, our phone messaging system, our website and our District and Campus Facebook pages.

We will also continue to offer lunches during this time for our students who qualify through the free/reduced lunch program.
Due to the fact that we will have very limited staff working in the District we ask that you communicate through e-mail.

Contact information:
James.skeeler@bosquevilleisd.org
Kelly.bray@bosquevilleisd.org
Cliff.heath@bosquevilleisd.org
Brian.vasek@bosquevilleisd.org
Rachel.carter@bosquevilleisd.org

Tomorrow we will honor Emmie’s heavenly birthday by wearing crazy socks. If you have socks to donate we will still be taking them.

On Saturday, from 2:00-4:00, we will have a packing celebration in the elementary cafeteria. We will pack individual pairs of socks and get them ready to distribute to different non-profit organizations. It’s a great event for kids to see how kindness can go a long way. I hope you can attend for at least a few minutes.

post_text: Today we honored one of our finest teachers by dedicating the Ag Building to Mr. Charles Prause. Before retiring in 2018, Mr. Prause made a positive impact and served as a mentor to countless students, staff, and fellow educators across this great state. The day was celebrated far and wide with family, former students, educators, and friends. Thank you, Mr. Prause, for your contributions to Bosqueville ISD!

Bosqueville FFA
April 18, 2019 at 9:16 PM ·

Results from Tarleton Area CDE Contest!
Farm Business Management place 5th and are headed to state in 2 weeks. Members were Hunter Heath, Adrian Amaro, Ian Hankhouse and Daniel Roe.
Floriculture placed 6th missing state by 1 place. Members were Emma Robertson, Hadleigh Gillett, Rachel Plank, and Morgan Rosanbalm.
Ag Mech placed 8th. Members were Eddy Dark(who was 9th high individual), Carson Skeeler, and Bo Ramos.
Horse placed 25th out of 48 teams. Members were Madison McKinney, Berkley Cowan, and Sophie Bawduniak.
Nursery/Landscape placed 11th. Members were Evette Garcia, Jordayn Criss, and Lauren McGee.
Poultry placed 11th out of 26 teams.
Members were Amanda Bruner, Summer Howard, Dalton Light, and Regan Roscher.

post_text: Congratulations to the Class of 2018 Salutatorian and Valedictorian of Bosqueville High School! Cole Walts is a National Honor Society member and honor graduate who will begin his post-secondary education at the University of Texas pursuing a degree in Sustainability Studies. Chelsea Nicholson has the highest average in the class, is an honor graduate, a member of the National Honor Society, and will attend Texas A&M to pursue a Doctorate in Veterinary Medicine. Best of luck on the next step in your journey!

Pictured with 200 pair of new athletic shoes are McGregor Bulldog High School Fellowship of Christian Athletes members Cade Zacharias, Kaylen Sloan, and Caleb Jones, and Bosqueville Bulldog High School Fellowship of Christian Athletes members Emma Grace Carpenter, Emma Robertson, and Luke Bradshaw.

The two F.C.A.s collected these shoes from donations made by the people of McGregor and Bosqueville in response to the “Shoes for Orphan Souls” campaign, which is sponsored by Buckner International of Dallas. Each year Buckner sends thousands of shoes to orphans around the world, and this is the fourth year the Fellowship of Christian Athletes has participated.

post_text: On Wednesday, the junior class traveled to the University of Houston for a campus visit funded by a grant awarded to Mrs. Granger by the University. Students were provided a college dining experience at the Moody Towers Dining Hall. A presentation about the university and the admissions process was followed by a campus tour. Along the tour students learned about the different colleges and programs within the university. They even learned a little about the mascot and were taught a traditional cougar yell. They visited a traditional dorm room, the M.D. Anderson Library and the student center. The tour was very helpful in showing the students the typical college campus and expectations for entering college.

Today is the annual BISD Homecoming Parade starting at 2PM. The parade will start at Keys Creek and proceed to the football field for the Homecoming Pep Rally. Each grade level has a float to ride.

In the event of inclement weather, the parade will stop and unload in front of the gym for an indoor pep rally.

Parents that are helping to decorate or load floats SHOULD NOT park in Keys Creek. Those cars should be parked in the high school parking lot. Parking for the pep rally is at the football field as well . There will be staff present to help direct floats and traffic.

Please be aware of students unloading floats and spectators walking to the field from the parade route.

We hope to see you there!

A schedule is provided below. All Testers need to report to their scheduled location at normal school hours 7:57am.

post_text: Thank you to our community for this wonderful historical video
shared_text:
Randall Scott‎Bosqueville High School
December 8, 2016 at 9:33 PM · College Station, TX ·

I went to Bosqueville School in 1965-1969, and then on to China Spring. I am the moderator of a Facebook group called "Historical Bosqueville (pre-1965)". We recently produced a video about Bosqueville School comprised of photo contributions from our members. At the moderators discretion, I would like to post that video here. There is an amazing story behind Bosqueville School.

Also, if you love Bosqueville and history, I would like to invite you to join us! Use the link below:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/historicalbosquevilletexas/

Come meet your child's teachers and discover how you can help your child have a successful school year! We will run an abbreviated schedule with 7 minute classes and 5 minute passing periods. Approximate start time 7:30pm (starts after the varsity volleyball game)

post_text:
"Coffee With the Superintendent"

Parents and community members are invited to come to the Bosqueville ISD Administration Office on Thursday, September 24th from (7:30 am - 8:15 am) to meet James Skeeler, Bosqueville ISD Superintendent of Schools. Mr. Skeeler will give an update on the District as well as answer any questions you might have. Coffee/water and Donuts will be provided.

post_text:
Progress Reports were sent home today w/ students. Please review, sign, and return with your student by Friday (9/18). If you have questions or concerns about a grade please contact the teacher. Tutorials are available each morning at 7:30 AM and after school until 4:00 PM.

If you have a chance please support the Bosqueville Excellence in Education Foundation (BEEF) tomorrow night at the new Chick-Fil-A located at 901 S. 7th St. from 5 PM to 8 PM. Proceeds support teacher grants!

post_text:
Junior High and High School Pictures will be taken Tuesday -September 15th! Grades 6th-11th will be taking pictures and can bring their order form on picture day. The order form is on the Bosqueville website, if one did not make it home with your child.

Senior Pictures will be taken October 7th! If your senior would like to have their picture made on Tuesday they will just need to bring the form to the office that morning so we will know to call them to the library for their picture.
